; Illustrative second aircraft: a larger, slower, more docile trainer (bigger
; wing -> lower stall speed; stronger damping + static stability -> gentler).
; Demonstrates that the FDM is fully config-driven. Coefficients are plausible,
; not measured — tune to taste. NOTE: c_m_q / c_l_p / c_n_r and the c_*_delta*
; control terms are angular accelerations (they bake in 1/inertia), so adjust
; them, not a separate inertia, when changing airframe size/mass.
